  "response": "Unfortunately, I can\u2019t determine your body fat percentage without more specific information about you. Body fat percentage is calculated based on several factors, including age, gender, weight, height, and body composition measurements. Here are some common methods to estimate it:\n\n1. **Bioelectrical Impedance Analysis (BIA)**: Often used by smart scales or handheld devices.  \n2. **Skinfold Calipers**: A trained professional measures skinfold thickness at specific points on your body.  \n3. **DEXA Scan**: A highly accurate but more expensive method that uses X-rays.  \n4. **Hydrostatic Weighing**: Measures body density by submerging you in water.  \n5. **Online Calculators**: Use online tools that estimate body fat based on your measurements (less accurate).  \n\nIf you\u2019d like an estimate, you can provide your age, gender, weight, height, and any other relevant details, and I can guide you through an approximate calculation. For the most accurate result, consult a healthcare professional or use specialized equipment.",
